WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:05.960
Public presentation of the results
of the survey Measuring Financial
Literacy in the Republic of Croatia,
4 Febrruary 2016
Croatian National Bank

00:00:07.400 --> 00:00:09.680
Hello everyone.

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:17.440
Ladies and
gentlemen, guests,

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:21.920
representatives of the ministries,
agencies, credit institutions,

00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:24.360
the media, the
academic community

00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:27.440
and civil society
and colleagues,

00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:31.160
I would like to wish
you a warm welcome

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:33.560
on behalf of the
Croatian National Bank

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:36.800
and the Croatian Financial
Services Supervisory Agency

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:39.720
at this presentation of the
results of a comprehensive survey

00:00:39.880 --> 00:00:42.960
of financial literacy in
the Republic of Croatia,

00:00:43.120 --> 00:00:49.360
initiated by the CNB and Hanfa and
conducted by the agency IPSOS.

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:53.080
Before we start, let me just
make a small technical remark.

00:00:53.240 --> 00:00:56.000
We have provided
headsets for all of you

00:00:56.160 --> 00:01:00.000
for better listenability in the
specific acoustic environment

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:02.560
of this beautiful
historical hall,

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:04.920
so they are available,

00:01:05.080 --> 00:01:08.800
I believe you will be able
to hear better with them.

00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:12.080
Before we turn to the
presentation of the results,

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:15.000
the benefits and the
scope of this survey,

00:01:15.160 --> 00:01:18.240
please allow me to have
the hosts of today's gathering

00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:20.320
extend a few
words of welcome.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:22.880
I would therefore first
like to ask the Governor

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:27.400
of the Croatian National Bank,
Mr Boris Vujčić to take the floor.

00:01:31.160 --> 00:01:33.600
Hello everyone.

00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:37.880
Thank you all for
gathering here today

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:40.760
to hear the
presentation of the results

00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:44.640
of the project that we have been
working on for quite some time

00:01:44.800 --> 00:01:47.360
and which we are
now proud to present,

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:50.840
the project of
measuring financial literacy

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.280
in the Republic
of Croatia.

00:01:53.440 --> 00:01:56.720
As I am sure you know from
your own personal experience,

00:01:56.880 --> 00:02:03.360
education in most areas starts
from an early age, in the family.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.400
This is where we learn our
first letters and numbers.

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:09.600
When we
start school,

00:02:09.760 --> 00:02:12.640
the educational system
takes over the responsibility

00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:15.240
for this type
of literacy.

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:18.280
However, when it
comes to financial literacy,

00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:21.720
things are a little different,
especially in Croatia,

00:02:21.880 --> 00:02:25.320
which is only starting to
develop systematic activities

00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:27.680
for building
financial literacy,

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:31.440
which means that we are now
in some sort of initial phase

00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:35.200
of developing
a systematic model

00:02:35.360 --> 00:02:43.000
for building financial literacy
from school age and beyond.

00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:48.040
Being aware of this,
we cannot be surprised

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:52.000
by the average score of
financial literacy of our citizens

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:54.480
determined
by this survey,

00:02:54.640 --> 00:02:57.160
which will be
explained in more detail

00:02:57.320 --> 00:02:59.600
by our research
team later on.

00:02:59.760 --> 00:03:01.840
I do not want
to prejudice

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:05.200
the interesting
findings they will present.

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:08.880
Financial literacy provides us
with fundamental knowledge

00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:12.840
about the functioning of the
economic and financial system

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:17.040
and an understanding of terms
such as inflation, exchange rate,

00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:20.680
external debt,
rating etc.

00:03:20.840 --> 00:03:23.320
We at the CNB are
particularly happy

00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:26.160
about the somewhat
better survey results

00:03:26.320 --> 00:03:28.880
in connection with
the main objective

00:03:29.040 --> 00:03:32.840
of the Croatian National
Bank, and that is price stability.

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:37.800
As you will see, 74% of citizens
know how inflation affects their lives

00:03:37.960 --> 00:03:42.440
and are familiar with
the basic characteristics

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:46.160
of what we
call inflation.

00:03:46.680 --> 00:03:51.560
In Croatia, we certainly owe that
in part to historical circumstances,

00:03:51.720 --> 00:03:54.280
which have taught
us many lessons,

00:03:54.440 --> 00:03:57.960
but probably also to the
enthusiasm of many teachers

00:03:58.120 --> 00:04:01.040
who have been bringing
their pupils and students

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:04.680
to the Croatian National Bank
over the past fifteen years or so,

00:04:04.840 --> 00:04:08.200
so they can learn first-hand
more about the work of the CNB,

00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:11.080
as well as to the
endeavours of the central bank

00:04:11.240 --> 00:04:15.960
to use this avenue to
educate the public about its activity.

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:18.240
Also, recognition
of the risks

00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:21.200
associated with the
management of personal finances

00:04:21.360 --> 00:04:25.120
is a very important
part of financial literacy,

00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:29.520
even though it does not fall
directly in the purview of the CNB,

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:33.560
but this aspect of financial literacy
is also important for us at the CNB

00:04:33.720 --> 00:04:37.760
as sound financial judgement
and decisions taken by individuals

00:04:37.920 --> 00:04:41.640
are associated with the
overall stability of the system,

00:04:41.800 --> 00:04:47.400
one of the key tasks with which the
Croatian National Bank is charged.

00:04:47.560 --> 00:04:50.160
We believe that
this survey gives us

00:04:50.320 --> 00:04:54.160
a clear picture of financial
literacy in our country

00:04:54.320 --> 00:04:58.400
and that its results will
provide a good starting point

00:04:58.560 --> 00:05:02.680
for further joint learning by
institutions and civil society

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:06.040
about the priority of
this type of education

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:08.800
and then for a
systematic formulation

00:05:08.960 --> 00:05:13.040
of educational programmes
in the context of the action plan

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:17.600
for the promotion of
consumer financial literacy.

00:05:17.760 --> 00:05:21.160
We have to bear
in mind, however,

00:05:21.320 --> 00:05:25.080
that financial literacy
and financial behaviour

00:05:25.240 --> 00:05:28.040
do not always
go hand in hand.

00:05:28.200 --> 00:05:31.240
The fact that a person
knows there is a risk involved

00:05:31.400 --> 00:05:34.280
does not mean that this
person will not take on that risk

00:05:34.440 --> 00:05:36.680
if they expect to
reap a benefit from it

00:05:36.840 --> 00:05:39.760
or if it is motivating
in some other way.

00:05:39.920 --> 00:05:42.960
This is confirmed in the
survey, as you will see,

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:45.320
by the low
correlation

00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:49.040
between financial knowledge
and behaviour revealed.

00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:51.720
I would like to
thank our colleagues

00:05:51.880 --> 00:05:55.160
from the Croatian Financial
Services Supervisory Agency

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:59.320
and stress the key importance
of our cooperation as regulators

00:05:59.480 --> 00:06:03.000
on such projects with
actors in the same market.

00:06:03.160 --> 00:06:05.520
We will continue to
work in this direction.

00:06:05.680 --> 00:06:08.240
Financial literacy is
an important issue

00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:10.520
for both our
institutions

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:14.880
and as the results of this survey will
show, there is room for education.

00:06:15.040 --> 00:06:17.320
I would also like to
thank the agency IPSOS

00:06:17.480 --> 00:06:19.880
for its brilliant
cooperation in this survey

00:06:20.040 --> 00:06:23.720
and the Ministry of
Finance for its support

00:06:23.880 --> 00:06:27.640
as a coordinator of these
activities in the Republic of Croatia.

00:06:27.800 --> 00:06:31.800
And once again,
thank you all for coming.

00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:41.880
Thank you,
Governor Vujčić.

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:44.800
The other host
of today's event,

00:06:44.960 --> 00:06:49.080
Mr Petar-Pierre Matek,
President of the Board of Hanfa.

00:06:49.240 --> 00:06:52.400
Mr Matek, please
take the floor.

00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:04.000
Ladies and gentlemen,
thank you all for coming.

00:07:04.160 --> 00:07:08.240
My thanks also go to all of those
who have put their time and energy

00:07:08.400 --> 00:07:11.240
into this
initiative, a starting,

00:07:11.400 --> 00:07:18.200
zero point, of a sort, for measuring
financial literacy in Croatia.

00:07:18.440 --> 00:07:21.400
As Governor
Vujčić has said,

00:07:21.560 --> 00:07:25.840
it should be used
as the foundation

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:30.520
for formulating an
optimal action plan

00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:33.600
for financial
education in the future

00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:38.320
and it should also
serve as a measure

00:07:38.480 --> 00:07:41.760
which will help us in
several years to measure

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:48.440
if we have made any headway and
improved financial literacy or not.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:52.080
As you have seen over
the past several years,

00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:55.320
financial literacy is being
increasingly talked about.

00:07:55.480 --> 00:07:57.680
I am particularly
pleased to see

00:07:57.840 --> 00:08:00.320
that more actions are
being taken in this area

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:03.000
and that it is not just a
subject of discussion.

00:08:03.160 --> 00:08:05.640
We are witnessing an
increased involvement

00:08:05.800 --> 00:08:08.760
of government institutions
and civil society representatives,

00:08:08.920 --> 00:08:11.720
as well as some initiatives
by the academic circles

00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:14.040
and there are some
private initiatives.

00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:16.360
This survey, as has
already been stated,

00:08:16.520 --> 00:08:19.120
is the result of a
joint effort by the CNB,

00:08:19.280 --> 00:08:22.200
Hanfa and the
Ministry of Finance.

00:08:22.360 --> 00:08:25.800
Financial literacy is
an imperative today.

00:08:25.960 --> 00:08:29.200
This means possessing the
necessary fundamental knowledge

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:33.960
to understand financial products
that are being offered to us

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:36.120
and which are
all around us,

00:08:36.280 --> 00:08:38.880
but perhaps an even
more important dimension

00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:43.240
is a rational attitude and a
rational behaviour towards money,

00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:50.120
which are acquired, as we all
agree, from early childhood.

00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:54.560
Both Hanfa and the CNB
are working continuously

00:08:54.720 --> 00:08:58.600
on the education
of the public.

00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:03.560
Some of our activities received
quite good media coverage;

00:09:03.720 --> 00:09:07.000
for instance, our
recent internet campaign

00:09:07.160 --> 00:09:10.880
warning of the risks of
complex financial products

00:09:11.040 --> 00:09:13.640
and our
educational pamphlets.

00:09:13.800 --> 00:09:18.680
This is the result of our long
and continuous intensive work

00:09:18.840 --> 00:09:22.120
with secondary schools,
various universities

00:09:22.280 --> 00:09:25.400
and institutions of higher
learning which come to visit us

00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:29.720
or in which we
often hold lectures.

00:09:29.880 --> 00:09:33.480
We are determined to
continue working in this area

00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:39.160
because it is of key importance
in a broader social context.

00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:43.880
I wish to thank the staff
of the IPSOS agency

00:09:44.040 --> 00:09:46.840
that have participated in
the survey and all of you

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:49.120
who have
gathered here today

00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:51.840
and I would now like to
give the floor to the people

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:55.480
who will present and show you
the results of this survey in detail.

00:09:55.640 --> 00:09:57.760
Thank you.

00:10:05.600 --> 00:10:08.320
The survey Measuring
Financial Literacy

00:10:08.480 --> 00:10:10.880
was conducted jointly
by Hanfa and the CNB,

00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:14.400
in cooperation with the Ministry of
Finance of the Republic of Croatia,

00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:17.040
the coordinating body
for all the activities

00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:20.160
in the area of financial
literacy in our country,

00:10:20.320 --> 00:10:22.560
based on the
2015 Action Plan

00:10:22.720 --> 00:10:26.160
for improving
consumer financial literacy.

00:10:26.320 --> 00:10:29.440
Here today with us is, therefore,
Mrs Ivana Ravlić Ivanović,

00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:31.840
the Head of the
Financial System Sector

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:34.560
of the Ministry of Finance
of the Republic of Croatia.

00:10:34.720 --> 00:10:37.800
Mrs Ravlić Ivanović,
please take the floor.

00:10:41.280 --> 00:10:43.760
Hello everyone. I would
like to extend my greetings

00:10:43.920 --> 00:10:46.080
to all of you on behalf
of the Ministry of Finance.

00:10:46.240 --> 00:10:49.120
I am very pleased to be here
today and to see so many of you

00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:51.280
who have
gathered here today

00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:53.760
to see this presentation
on financial literacy,

00:10:53.920 --> 00:10:56.760
which has justifiably
been gaining in importance

00:10:56.920 --> 00:11:00.840
over the past several
years. In this context,

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:05.040
the Ministry of Finance brought
together in the past several years,

00:11:05.200 --> 00:11:09.560
or more precisely in 2014, a wide
circle of actors, from, naturally

00:11:09.720 --> 00:11:13.760
government bodies, from
the non-government sector

00:11:13.920 --> 00:11:17.200
and professional
organisations and associations,

00:11:17.360 --> 00:11:21.080
as well as from consumer
protection organisations,

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:25.520
in a joint effort to draw up a
national strategic framework

00:11:25.680 --> 00:11:31.280
of financial literacy in
the 2015 to 2020 period.

00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:35.240
In early 2015, the Government
of the Republic of Croatia

00:11:35.400 --> 00:11:37.880
adopted this document, which
as such provides the basis

00:11:38.040 --> 00:11:42.160
for the development of
financial literacy in Croatia.

00:11:42.320 --> 00:11:47.760
It should be noted that an
accompanying action plan for 2015

00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:53.440
was prepared,
determining the activities

00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:58.400
to be taken by
individual bodies

00:11:58.560 --> 00:12:02.160
for the purpose of
promoting financial literacy.

00:12:02.320 --> 00:12:06.760
One of the key activities
determined under this plan

00:12:06.920 --> 00:12:10.480
was this survey
of financial literacy,

00:12:10.640 --> 00:12:15.280
the responsibility for which
was assigned to our regulators,

00:12:15.440 --> 00:12:17.480
the Croatian
National Bank

00:12:17.640 --> 00:12:21.480
and the Croatian Financial
Services Supervisory Agency.

00:12:21.640 --> 00:12:24.240
In this context, this
extremely important activity

00:12:24.400 --> 00:12:27.920
is a step in the
right direction

00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:31.480
and its results will serve as
a basis for further activities

00:12:31.640 --> 00:12:36.680
and for piloting the entire
project in the right direction.

00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:40.880
I would like to use this
opportunity to stress

00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:43.000
that the Republic of Croatia,

00:12:43.160 --> 00:12:46.160
together with the bodies
involved in this project,

00:12:46.320 --> 00:12:49.040
has in the past
several years undertaken

00:12:49.200 --> 00:12:51.480
a significant
number of activities.

00:12:51.640 --> 00:12:54.480
This was recognised by
the non-profit organisation

00:12:54.640 --> 00:12:57.960
Child and Youth Finance
International which nominated us

00:12:58.120 --> 00:13:00.600
for an award as a
country, i.e. the bodies

00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:04.720
that had really taken a significant
number of activities in this area.

00:13:04.880 --> 00:13:08.080
In addition to Croatia,
other countries nominated

00:13:08.240 --> 00:13:13.320
for this annual award were
Great Britain, Italy and Turkey.

00:13:13.480 --> 00:13:17.240
We did not get the
award. It went to Turkey.

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:20.440
We were close and this
proves that all these activities

00:13:20.600 --> 00:13:27.040
that we have been taking are
a step in the right direction.

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:30.000
What I would
also like to stress is

00:13:30.160 --> 00:13:34.040
that we are very
eager to see the results

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:37.520
that will be
presented here today,

00:13:37.680 --> 00:13:40.560
and especially to
have them analysed.

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:44.760
There is a working group operating
with the Ministry of Finance

00:13:44.920 --> 00:13:49.400
which is responsible for financial
literacy and the related measures

00:13:49.560 --> 00:13:53.960
and activities and I see many
representatives here today

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:57.800
involved in the work of the working
group and I am happy to see

00:13:57.960 --> 00:14:00.240
that most of you
are present here.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:03.480
One of our next steps will
be to combine our efforts

00:14:03.640 --> 00:14:07.280
in order to analyse the results
that will be presented today

00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:11.240
and to channel our
activities and measures

00:14:11.400 --> 00:14:15.360
towards the most
vulnerable groups,

00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:21.800
so as to improve and
increase their financial literacy.

00:14:21.960 --> 00:14:24.240
Thank you.

00:14:31.400 --> 00:14:35.120
Both the Croatian National Bank
and Hanfa are working continuously

00:14:35.280 --> 00:14:38.520
on the financial literacy
of the general public

00:14:38.680 --> 00:14:43.200
so it is only logical that
they have joined forces

00:14:43.360 --> 00:14:45.680
in the approach to
this survey project.

00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:48.720
Mrs Silvana Božić, a
member of the Board of Hanfa

00:14:48.880 --> 00:14:50.840
will now speak

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:54.600
on behalf of the Croatian Financial
Services Supervisory Agency.

00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:56.720
Thank you.
Hello everyone.

00:14:56.880 --> 00:14:59.520
It is nice to see you in
such a large number.

00:14:59.680 --> 00:15:02.400
This gives me the
hope and reassurance

00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:05.000
that there is a
clear understanding

00:15:05.160 --> 00:15:08.960
that it is vital to achieve
or reach an adequate level

00:15:09.120 --> 00:15:12.720
of financial literacy
among Croatian citizens

00:15:12.880 --> 00:15:16.080
and that all of you
present here today

00:15:16.240 --> 00:15:22.400
are ready to participate actively in
the achievement of this objective,

00:15:22.560 --> 00:15:25.800
each of us within our own
spheres of competence

00:15:25.960 --> 00:15:29.080
and business activity but
also through joint actions,

00:15:29.240 --> 00:15:31.200
in the creation
of an environment

00:15:31.360 --> 00:15:33.960
conducive to raising the
level of financial literacy.

00:15:34.120 --> 00:15:37.880
Work in the area of financial
literacy is actually not a project.

00:15:38.040 --> 00:15:41.480
It is a long-term process,
and an extremely complex one.

00:15:41.640 --> 00:15:46.120
It requires extraordinary
efforts, both human and financial,

00:15:46.280 --> 00:15:50.520
and credible
sources of information

00:15:50.680 --> 00:15:54.000
based on which the
objectives are defined.

00:15:54.160 --> 00:15:56.760
The same is true of
the selection methods.

00:15:56.920 --> 00:16:00.160
And this is what we
all need to understand,

00:16:00.320 --> 00:16:03.200
that it is a
process that will last

00:16:03.360 --> 00:16:07.920
and will only show results
in the medium or the long term,

00:16:08.080 --> 00:16:13.040
and that we should persist in
our efforts and continue to focus

00:16:13.200 --> 00:16:15.960
and work diligently and
continuously on this issue.

00:16:16.120 --> 00:16:20.320
As for Hanfa, since Mrs Ravlić
has provided the time frame

00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:24.480
in connection with the national
framework of financial literacy,

00:16:24.640 --> 00:16:28.920
I would like to turn to
our activities in which,

00:16:29.080 --> 00:16:33.640
while analysing the ways of
reaching the target audience,

00:16:33.800 --> 00:16:36.400
our users of
financial services,

00:16:36.560 --> 00:16:39.760
we examined the possible
avenues and the media

00:16:39.920 --> 00:16:42.720
that could help us reach
our audience efficiently.

00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:47.760
Among other things, we analysed
different global trends and actions

00:16:47.920 --> 00:16:54.360
taken by other regulators,
as well as OECD analyses,

00:16:54.520 --> 00:17:01.280
and in cooperation
with Hanfa's expert teams

00:17:01.440 --> 00:17:05.920
and marketing agencies,
steered our activities.

00:17:06.080 --> 00:17:10.480
Actually, when
analysing all these materials,

00:17:10.640 --> 00:17:15.120
we discovered that it is
vital to select good media

00:17:15.280 --> 00:17:17.800
and a good channel
of communication

00:17:17.960 --> 00:17:23.880
otherwise the information
sent to the target audience

00:17:24.040 --> 00:17:29.320
is quickly lost if it is not
presented in an interactive way

00:17:29.480 --> 00:17:34.360
or not provided to the
users when they need it.

00:17:34.520 --> 00:17:42.240
With that in mind, we focused
our activities on several areas,

00:17:42.400 --> 00:17:48.360
from the production of brochures
explaining in simple terms

00:17:48.520 --> 00:17:51.600
the financial
concepts and areas

00:17:51.760 --> 00:17:54.760
which fall within
Hanfa's area of competence

00:17:54.920 --> 00:18:01.240
to web postings of
educational content or warnings

00:18:01.400 --> 00:18:05.880
aimed at drawing the attention
of users of financial services

00:18:06.040 --> 00:18:09.920
to the possibilities
and the risks

00:18:10.080 --> 00:18:13.880
involved in transactions
with financial intermediaries.

00:18:14.040 --> 00:18:17.240
We also used
what is for regulators

00:18:17.400 --> 00:18:22.160
a relatively new channel of
communication with users,

00:18:22.320 --> 00:18:28.480
the Internet, launching
a campaign on the Internet

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:34.880
and in the daily press
to send out messages

00:18:35.040 --> 00:18:39.920
to users of
financial services.

00:18:40.080 --> 00:18:44.120
At the same time, we
actually infiltrated the web

00:18:44.280 --> 00:18:48.720
through web advertising in order
to come as close as possible

00:18:48.880 --> 00:18:53.360
to today's users of
financial services.

00:18:53.520 --> 00:18:56.760
By doing so, we were able
to target a wider audience,

00:18:56.920 --> 00:19:01.880
making sure that different needs of
individual target groups were met,

00:19:02.040 --> 00:19:05.760
as they all do make up
a very diverse group,

00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:11.120
so we worked in parallel with
secondary schools and universities,

00:19:11.280 --> 00:19:17.200
organising tailor-made workshops,
covering topics of their interest;

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:23.720
from debates at various universities
in connection with pension funds

00:19:23.880 --> 00:19:27.240
to a pilot project in
cooperation with colleagues

00:19:27.400 --> 00:19:29.480
from the Zagreb
Stock Exchange

00:19:29.640 --> 00:19:32.520
and the Croatian Chamber of
Economy in which we tested

00:19:32.680 --> 00:19:35.760
the possibility for educating small
and medium-sized entrepreneurs

00:19:35.920 --> 00:19:38.360
in considering
sources of financing

00:19:38.520 --> 00:19:42.200
other than those
commonly offered by banks.

00:19:42.360 --> 00:19:48.840
So, this process of financial literacy
is extremely complex and layered

00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:52.560
and requires a lot of
commitment and hard thinking

00:19:52.720 --> 00:19:56.160
on to how best reach
the target audience.

00:19:56.320 --> 00:20:01.120
What I would like to stress here and
what makes us particularly happy is

00:20:01.280 --> 00:20:06.000
the growing interest of young
people in financial topics,

00:20:06.160 --> 00:20:08.240
from those of
general nature

00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:13.680
to those relating to capital market
developments, securities trading,

00:20:13.840 --> 00:20:16.720
the functioning of
the stock exchange,

00:20:16.880 --> 00:20:19.240
selection of
pension funds,

00:20:19.400 --> 00:20:24.800
as you will see in the
presentation of the survey

00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:28.080
but I will leave the
details to Mr Dumičić.

00:20:28.240 --> 00:20:31.320
In terms of their
knowledge, behaviour

00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:33.920
and attitude
towards money,

00:20:34.080 --> 00:20:37.360
the young are actually
the most vulnerable group

00:20:37.520 --> 00:20:39.840
and it is the
responsibility of all of us

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:43.320
who are a little more
experienced to empower them

00:20:43.480 --> 00:20:46.400
for their future
and enable them

00:20:46.560 --> 00:20:48.960
to respond adequately
to the challenges

00:20:49.120 --> 00:20:51.720
of making financial
decisions. In this context,

00:20:51.880 --> 00:20:55.720
Hanfa will continue
to pursue its projects,

00:20:55.880 --> 00:20:59.920
aiming both at the general
public and especially the young,

00:21:00.080 --> 00:21:04.320
since they have a longer life and
business careers ahead of them

00:21:04.480 --> 00:21:10.080
during which period they are bound
to have numerous financial needs

00:21:10.240 --> 00:21:13.360
and will come across
numerous financial possibilities

00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:17.240
that they will have to understand
and be able to assess them

00:21:17.400 --> 00:21:20.880
at a certain point in
their lives, even more so

00:21:21.040 --> 00:21:26.200
if we take into account the growing
complexity of financial products

00:21:26.360 --> 00:21:32.360
and services offered
individually or in packages,

00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:38.680
as we witness various combinations
of savings and deposit products,

00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:44.000
deposit combinations,
derivatives, insurance funds,

00:21:44.160 --> 00:21:50.560
all being made more complex
and challenging by the fact

00:21:50.720 --> 00:21:55.040
that a growing number of
financial services and products

00:21:55.200 --> 00:22:00.280
are offered through the
Internet and web portals,

00:22:00.440 --> 00:22:04.400
and these services are
being increasingly digitalised

00:22:04.560 --> 00:22:08.480
as a result of
technological development.

00:22:08.640 --> 00:22:11.600
Their distribution and
marketing are being transferred

00:22:11.760 --> 00:22:15.080
into the digital world, a fact which
also poses additional challenges

00:22:15.240 --> 00:22:18.280
for the regulators in the context
of identification of the risks

00:22:18.440 --> 00:22:21.960
arising from such a model of
distribution and marketing,

00:22:22.120 --> 00:22:27.640
and to respond to these new trends
in an adequate and timely manner.

00:22:27.800 --> 00:22:30.760
Therefore, I think
that our cooperation

00:22:30.920 --> 00:22:34.520
and exchange of experience
with the CNB is a good thing

00:22:34.680 --> 00:22:40.560
as it enables us to come up with
optimal forms of further action

00:22:40.720 --> 00:22:43.200
in the field of
financial literacy.

00:22:43.360 --> 00:22:47.480
We are also very happy to see
many other actors participating

00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:53.160
in this effort through the national
financial literacy framework,

00:22:53.320 --> 00:22:58.480
including the efforts of our
colleagues in the ministries

00:22:58.640 --> 00:23:01.840
and agencies responsible
for formal education

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:06.520
and of the numerous professional
associations and organisations

00:23:06.680 --> 00:23:09.880
aimed at increasing

00:23:10.040 --> 00:23:13.680
the overall financial
literacy of Croatian citizens.

00:23:13.840 --> 00:23:18.560
So much from me for now. Now
I give the floor to our colleagues.

00:23:25.520 --> 00:23:27.760
Financial knowledge

00:23:27.920 --> 00:23:31.480
is one of the main
components of financial literacy

00:23:31.640 --> 00:23:36.800
and its elements largely fall
within the purview of the CNB.

00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:39.960
Therefore, we have here
with us today Mr Bojan Fras,

00:23:40.120 --> 00:23:42.280
Vice Governor of the
Croatian National Bank

00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:44.440
responsible,
among other things,

00:23:44.600 --> 00:23:47.600
for the monitoring of consumer
protection in banks. Mr Fras...

00:23:47.760 --> 00:23:49.640
Thank you.
Hello everyone.

00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:52.680
I think that my
colleague speakers covered

00:23:52.840 --> 00:23:56.920
most of the general introductory
remarks pertaining to the topic.

00:23:57.080 --> 00:24:00.840
Maybe just a few
remarks in conclusion,

00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:03.800
before I leave the
floor to Mr Dumičić.

00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:07.560
Having heard all these
arguments, it is difficult to imagine

00:24:07.720 --> 00:24:11.160
or pick out a group of people
that would not be concerned

00:24:11.320 --> 00:24:13.400
by the issue of
financial literacy.

00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:16.440
Obviously, life is getting more
complex and financial products

00:24:16.600 --> 00:24:19.040
and services are
getting more complex

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:22.960
and this requires an adequate
response from the regulators

00:24:23.120 --> 00:24:26.560
and the actors involved
in the provision of such services.

00:24:26.720 --> 00:24:30.440
And it is interesting that the sample
of guests present here today

00:24:30.600 --> 00:24:34.680
is an atypical sample of
people normally attending events

00:24:34.840 --> 00:24:41.240
hosted by regulators such as the
Croatian National Bank or Hanfa.

00:24:41.400 --> 00:24:46.240
We have here today with us the
representatives of civil society

00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:49.880
and civil society organisations,
consumer organisations,

00:24:50.040 --> 00:24:54.920
the academic
community, researchers, etc.

00:24:55.080 --> 00:24:58.800
This is a sample
atypical for this institution

00:24:58.960 --> 00:25:01.240
and we are all
very happy about it

00:25:01.400 --> 00:25:04.400
because it creates new potential
for cooperation and research

00:25:04.560 --> 00:25:09.040
and a more focused joint
approach to this objective.

00:25:09.200 --> 00:25:14.080
What is characteristic of
us in this field in Croatia

00:25:14.240 --> 00:25:18.000
is the tradition of working in a
culture marked by high inflation.

00:25:18.160 --> 00:25:22.640
This tradition has been inherited
by only one part of the population

00:25:22.800 --> 00:25:25.680
and what the Governor
pointed out in the introduction,

00:25:25.840 --> 00:25:29.520
that 74% or 75% of
respondents were aware of

00:25:29.680 --> 00:25:33.000
or understood the
effects of inflation,

00:25:33.160 --> 00:25:37.120
indicates in fact that a
significant part of the sample,

00:25:37.280 --> 00:25:41.000
or a significant
portion of our population,

00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:43.600
is still unfamiliar with
inflation and its effects.

00:25:43.760 --> 00:25:46.400
What I want to say is
that times have changed

00:25:46.560 --> 00:25:49.000
and the knowledge
acquired in one period

00:25:49.160 --> 00:25:52.800
does not necessarily meet the
challenges of the new period,

00:25:52.960 --> 00:25:58.720
and the younger generations,
that have very significant results

00:25:58.880 --> 00:26:03.680
in a negative sense in the
survey, have to work much harder

00:26:03.840 --> 00:26:07.880
to catch up with
previous generations,

00:26:08.040 --> 00:26:10.880
such as my generation
and the generation before,

00:26:11.040 --> 00:26:13.880
which had to cope in
conditions of high inflation

00:26:14.040 --> 00:26:18.440
and the pegging of their personal
finances to a foreign currency.

00:26:20.640 --> 00:26:23.120
The regulators are
naturally interested

00:26:23.280 --> 00:26:26.040
in raising the level
of financial literacy

00:26:26.200 --> 00:26:28.520
and in fact their efforts
are complementary

00:26:28.680 --> 00:26:31.840
to the endeavours of industry,
consumer organisations

00:26:32.000 --> 00:26:35.240
and other actors
taking part in this process.

00:26:35.400 --> 00:26:38.880
And let us now turn
briefly to the survey.

00:26:39.040 --> 00:26:43.000
I think we have to say that,
even though financial literacy

00:26:43.160 --> 00:26:46.200
is a new phenomenon
being researched in our field,

00:26:46.360 --> 00:26:50.320
we have to say that this is
not the first survey conducted,

00:26:50.480 --> 00:26:53.200
although it is key in
terms of its importance.

00:26:53.360 --> 00:26:56.560
The first survey was
conducted by our colleagues,

00:26:56.720 --> 00:26:59.920
a team from the Institute
of Economics, Zagreb,

00:27:00.080 --> 00:27:04.080
led by Professor Maja Vehovec.
A little less than a year ago

00:27:04.240 --> 00:27:07.240
we had the opportunity
to see their results.

00:27:07.400 --> 00:27:10.960
Although the sample used in their
research was somewhat smaller

00:27:11.120 --> 00:27:15.560
and the methodology different, I
think it was a valuable contribution,

00:27:15.720 --> 00:27:19.840
spearheading the investigation of
these phenomena in our country.

00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:22.880
And finally, I would
like to say something

00:27:23.040 --> 00:27:25.280
about the activities of the
Croatian National Bank

00:27:25.440 --> 00:27:30.280
in connection with financial literacy
and enhancing financial literacy.

00:27:30.440 --> 00:27:32.520
I must say
I am very pleased

00:27:32.680 --> 00:27:39.360
that our institutional
intuition was sound, good.

00:27:39.520 --> 00:27:41.920
By the
institutional intuition,

00:27:42.080 --> 00:27:45.120
I mean that even without
the results of this survey,

00:27:45.280 --> 00:27:49.960
the activities taken by the CNB up
to now aimed at financial education,

00:27:50.120 --> 00:27:52.360
were actually
very well focused;

00:27:52.520 --> 00:27:56.320
they were mainly targeted
towards younger individuals,

00:27:56.480 --> 00:28:00.880
i.e. pupils in their final
years of secondary education

00:28:01.040 --> 00:28:04.440
and younger individuals in
general. Why this is important

00:28:04.600 --> 00:28:07.880
you will see in this
survey. In this group

00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:11.360
results proved to be
the most unsatisfactory.

00:28:11.520 --> 00:28:14.880
Accordingly, over
the past several years

00:28:15.040 --> 00:28:18.120
we have hosted a number
of different workshops

00:28:18.280 --> 00:28:21.360
attended by some 500
secondary school pupils

00:28:21.520 --> 00:28:26.200
with the aim of raising awareness
about the financial environment

00:28:26.360 --> 00:28:30.480
they will encounter once
they enter the labour market;

00:28:30.640 --> 00:28:33.920
they were 17- or
18-year-old students

00:28:34.080 --> 00:28:37.320
most of whom had not yet
entered the labour market.

00:28:37.480 --> 00:28:40.840
We intend to increase
our activities in this area

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:44.480
as this is clearly a step
in the right direction.

00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:47.920
As the Governor pointed out,
for some 15 years we have hosted

00:28:48.080 --> 00:28:51.960
specialised workshops and
lectures for college students.

00:28:52.120 --> 00:28:56.360
Just a few days ago we had
a group of students visiting

00:28:56.520 --> 00:28:59.480
and we discussed the
financial environment

00:28:59.640 --> 00:29:03.680
in which they will find themselves,
once they complete their studies.

00:29:03.840 --> 00:29:07.320
The survey to be
presented now is actually

00:29:07.480 --> 00:29:12.240
fundamental research into the
financial literacy of a country.

00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:17.440
It is made in accordance
with the OECD model,

00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:22.040
which not only enables
us to identify the areas

00:29:22.200 --> 00:29:26.880
which require more effort, or the
areas on which we should focus

00:29:27.040 --> 00:29:30.800
our financial education and
literacy improvement efforts,

00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:33.280
but it also gives
us the possibility

00:29:33.440 --> 00:29:36.400
to compare the
situation in our country

00:29:36.560 --> 00:29:39.840
and our accomplishments
thus far, with other countries,

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:42.480
as we will see
in the presentation.

00:29:42.640 --> 00:29:45.680
What we are looking
forward to in the future

00:29:45.840 --> 00:29:51.160
are activities that we will launch
with enthusiasm after this survey.

00:29:51.320 --> 00:29:56.360
Very soon, and this is an
announcement in that direction,

00:29:56.520 --> 00:29:59.400
we will have a new
Croatian National Bank website

00:29:59.560 --> 00:30:04.120
that will enable new functionalities
and provide new educational

00:30:04.280 --> 00:30:11.040
and other material for the financial
education of our consumers.

00:30:11.200 --> 00:30:16.840
The materials are already there,
much of them are already uploaded

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:21.800
and we are now waiting for the
opportunity to launch the website.

00:30:21.960 --> 00:30:26.120
Another activity that will probably
come as a natural follow-up

00:30:26.280 --> 00:30:29.280
to the activities taken so far
and the results of the survey

00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:32.880
is a cooperation with
secondary school teachers

00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:37.120
about the possible introduction of
some form of financial education

00:30:37.280 --> 00:30:42.440
into the curriculum. A public
discussion on that topic

00:30:42.600 --> 00:30:47.720
has been underway in the past year
and we look forward to its results.

00:30:47.880 --> 00:30:51.120
And finally, this survey
highlights the need

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:54.560
for a new agreement on
the direction to be taken

00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:58.640
by all the actors represented here
today, particularly the regulators,

00:30:58.800 --> 00:31:00.960
to improve
their activities

00:31:01.120 --> 00:31:04.240
in connection with financial
training and education.

00:31:04.400 --> 00:31:07.680
Thank you very much. I think
there is no point in my going further

00:31:07.840 --> 00:31:12.520
with general remarks, so I would
like to call on Mr Dumičić...

00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:20.760
And so we have come
to the survey itself,

00:31:20.920 --> 00:31:25.000
conducted by
face-to-face interviews,

00:31:25.160 --> 00:31:30.840
on a sample of over 1000
respondents aged 18 to 79.

00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:34.800
I would like to ask
Mr Srđan Dumičić,

00:31:34.960 --> 00:31:40.120
Managing Director of IPSOS, to
present the results of the survey.

00:31:40.280 --> 00:31:42.360
Please.

00:31:45.640 --> 00:31:48.400
Let me first welcome
everybody present.

00:31:48.560 --> 00:31:50.760
I would like to thank
the numerous organisers

00:31:50.920 --> 00:31:53.640
for the opportunity to
participate in the implementation

00:31:53.800 --> 00:31:55.880
and presentation
of such a fine survey

00:31:56.040 --> 00:32:00.280
and would like to thank the IPSOS
team involved in the preparation,

00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:04.680
the survey and this presentation,
Tanja, Gordan and Luka.

00:32:04.840 --> 00:32:09.360
They are here today so if there
are any additional questions,

00:32:09.520 --> 00:32:11.520
they will be able
to answer them.

00:32:11.680 --> 00:32:14.040
Now I would like to
start with the presentation

00:32:14.200 --> 00:32:16.280
of the results
of the survey.

00:32:16.440 --> 00:32:18.760
I will first say a few words
about the methodology

00:32:18.920 --> 00:32:21.920
and then about financial
literacy and its components

00:32:22.080 --> 00:32:24.840
and then about some
additional aspects

00:32:25.000 --> 00:32:29.040
of financial behaviour
of Croatian citizens.

00:32:29.200 --> 00:32:32.480
As regards the key information
about the methodology,

00:32:32.640 --> 00:32:36.840
Alemka has already mentioned
that the methodology used

00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:40.440
consisted of face-to-face
interviews in households.

00:32:40.600 --> 00:32:45.120
The respondents
surveyed were aged 18 to 79.

00:32:45.280 --> 00:32:48.960
This fact is important for
the analysis of the results.

00:32:49.120 --> 00:32:52.280
The sample included
approximately 1000 respondents

00:32:52.440 --> 00:32:55.000
and it was nationally
representative,

00:32:55.160 --> 00:32:58.840
which means that in terms of its
basic socio-demographic indicators

00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:03.000
it was representative of the
general population of Croatia.

00:33:03.160 --> 00:33:05.800
And of course, as
mentioned several times already,

00:33:05.960 --> 00:33:09.760
the objective of this research was
to investigate financial literacy,

00:33:09.920 --> 00:33:12.080
its components
and of course

00:33:12.240 --> 00:33:16.520
some other aspects of financial
behaviour of Croatian citizens.

00:33:16.680 --> 00:33:20.400
What does it mean that the sample
was nationally representative?

00:33:20.560 --> 00:33:24.600
This means that in terms of basic
socio-demographic characteristics

00:33:24.760 --> 00:33:29.480
such as gender, age, region,
income level, and town size,

00:33:29.640 --> 00:33:34.400
it approximates the structure
of Croatian population.

00:33:34.560 --> 00:33:37.880
However, it is not uncommon
for problems to emerge

00:33:38.040 --> 00:33:40.280
in the realisation
of the sample.

00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:43.920
Any smaller deviations
are adjusted by weights

00:33:44.080 --> 00:33:46.440
to the general
population.

00:33:46.600 --> 00:33:49.600
So the results obtained
are representative of

00:33:49.760 --> 00:33:53.640
and valid for the overall
Croatian population.

00:33:53.800 --> 00:33:57.080
And now we shall
start our main topic,

00:33:57.240 --> 00:34:00.200
and that is financial
literacy in Croatia.

00:34:00.360 --> 00:34:04.520
In this survey, as
mentioned several times,

00:34:04.680 --> 00:34:08.520
the OECD
methodology was used.

00:34:08.680 --> 00:34:12.240
We can say that a general
definition of financial literacy is

00:34:12.400 --> 00:34:15.880
that it is a combination of
awareness, knowledge, skills,

00:34:16.040 --> 00:34:21.880
attitudes and behaviour necessary
for making financial decisions.

00:34:22.040 --> 00:34:26.000
The higher the literacy, the
sounder the decisions will be

00:34:26.160 --> 00:34:28.640
for the individual
making them.

00:34:28.800 --> 00:34:32.480
According to the
OECD methodology,

00:34:37.240 --> 00:34:42.560
financial literacy is a composite
index consisting of 3 components.

00:34:42.720 --> 00:34:45.000
The first is
financial knowledge.

00:34:45.160 --> 00:34:49.200
It accounts for 33% of the
final result of financial literacy,

00:34:49.360 --> 00:34:51.520
the second is
financial behaviour

00:34:51.680 --> 00:34:54.480
which accounts for the largest
share, or 43% of the final result

00:34:54.640 --> 00:34:57.240
and the third is attitude
towards spending money.

00:34:57.400 --> 00:34:59.800
Each of these
components is defined

00:34:59.960 --> 00:35:02.800
by several
questions or tasks

00:35:02.960 --> 00:35:07.960
and a scoring system determined
by the OECD methodology.

00:35:08.120 --> 00:35:10.280
I would like to
stress here now

00:35:10.440 --> 00:35:13.120
that for full understanding
of some of the results

00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:15.400
and for a more
thorough analysis,

00:35:15.560 --> 00:35:18.720
it is essential to determine
exactly which these questions are

00:35:18.880 --> 00:35:23.280
and how these three components
and by extension, financial literacy,

00:35:23.440 --> 00:35:26.680
are defined, because this
helps in the actual understanding

00:35:26.840 --> 00:35:30.160
of all the results.
Sometimes these terms,

00:35:30.320 --> 00:35:34.160
financial knowledge and
behaviour, as used colloquially,

00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:38.280
differ from their definitions
in the survey's questions

00:35:38.440 --> 00:35:41.480
and tasks under
the OECD methodology.

00:35:41.640 --> 00:35:46.000
This methodology has been made
to be applicable across countries,

00:35:46.160 --> 00:35:49.280
regardless of their
social development, wealth,

00:35:49.440 --> 00:35:53.120
and other characteristics so we
have countries such as Malaysia,

00:35:53.280 --> 00:35:56.040
Bhutan, Uganda,
Norway, Germany, etc.,

00:35:56.200 --> 00:36:00.160
as well as mid-positioned
countries, such as our country.

00:36:00.320 --> 00:36:04.440
We see that under the
scoring system used,

00:36:04.600 --> 00:36:08.120
financial knowledge carries a
score of 7, behaviour a score of 9

00:36:08.280 --> 00:36:10.960
and attitude towards
money a score of 5,

00:36:11.120 --> 00:36:15.320
all giving a maximum score of
21 that a country or an individual

00:36:15.480 --> 00:36:19.120
may achieve in
financial literacy.

00:36:22.360 --> 00:36:27.040
The first component, the element
which determines financial literacy,

00:36:27.200 --> 00:36:30.240
is financial
knowledge.

00:36:30.400 --> 00:36:32.880
In this component,

00:36:33.040 --> 00:36:39.440
Croatian citizens scored an
average of 4.2 of the total of 7.

00:36:39.600 --> 00:36:44.400
This is a medium score,
slightly above average.

00:36:44.560 --> 00:36:49.880
Younger citizens scored the lowest
in terms of financial knowledge,

00:36:50.040 --> 00:36:52.440
which can probably
be understood,

00:36:52.600 --> 00:36:56.680
followed by older
citizens, those aged over 70,

00:36:56.840 --> 00:36:58.960
which can also
be understood,

00:36:59.120 --> 00:37:01.840
as some of them no longer
have any interest in learning

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:04.120
and have never
learnt these things.

00:37:04.280 --> 00:37:07.040
People with lower education have
a lower level of financial knowledge

00:37:07.200 --> 00:37:10.040
and so do those with
household incomes

00:37:10.200 --> 00:37:14.800
below the threshold
of HRK 3750.

00:37:18.920 --> 00:37:21.880
There is another
point that we can make

00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:25.560
based on the questions
concerning financial knowledge.

00:37:25.720 --> 00:37:28.720
We can see that as
many as 74% of citizens

00:37:28.880 --> 00:37:33.360
are aware of the effect
of inflation on their lives.

00:37:33.520 --> 00:37:36.400
All the older
generations have learnt that

00:37:36.560 --> 00:37:39.360
and until recently we had
plenty of experience in this area.

00:37:39.520 --> 00:37:42.440
However, despite that, less
than one half of respondents

00:37:42.600 --> 00:37:45.360
were able to solve a
very simple inflation task.

00:37:45.520 --> 00:37:48.640
I have to stress here that
OECD questions are very simple

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:51.920
and so are the
statements, simple and basic,

00:37:52.080 --> 00:37:55.640
so much so that 80% of the
citizens understood the task

00:37:55.800 --> 00:37:59.640
requiring an understanding of
the concept of interest on a loan.

00:37:59.800 --> 00:38:02.800
This means that people are
aware that if they borrow money,

00:38:02.960 --> 00:38:06.080
there will be interest and they will
have to pay back more money.

00:38:06.240 --> 00:38:09.280
They understand that. As many
as two thirds of the citizens know

00:38:09.440 --> 00:38:11.680
how to calculate
simple interest.

00:38:11.840 --> 00:38:14.120
However, only one third
of the citizens know

00:38:14.280 --> 00:38:16.560
how to calculate
compound interest

00:38:16.720 --> 00:38:19.680
and around two thirds of
citizens are familiar with the fact

00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:24.440
that high yield is associated with
high risks and, in a similar vein,

00:38:24.600 --> 00:38:28.640
approximately two thirds
of the citizens are aware

00:38:28.800 --> 00:38:33.960
that diversification of
savings or investments

00:38:34.120 --> 00:38:40.240
provides a protection against
risks, which is a high percentage,

00:38:40.400 --> 00:38:44.440
and I would like to
refer to the statements

00:38:44.600 --> 00:38:47.480
in the OECD
questionnaire, where it says,

00:38:47.640 --> 00:38:51.600
"It is less likely that you
will lose all of your money

00:38:51.760 --> 00:38:55.080
if you save it in
more than one place."

00:38:55.240 --> 00:38:58.920
So, it is not a complex
question and I would say

00:38:59.080 --> 00:39:02.480
that it is an issue indeed that as
many as one third of the citizens

00:39:02.640 --> 00:39:05.920
do not understand the
concept of diversification.

00:39:06.080 --> 00:39:10.640
Knowledge accounts for
one third of financial literacy.

00:39:10.800 --> 00:39:16.240
The OECD has a measure used
for comparisons across countries;

00:39:16.400 --> 00:39:20.000
it is the percentage of
citizens that have scored high.

00:39:20.160 --> 00:39:23.560
In our case high scores were
defined by 6 and 7 and here,

00:39:23.720 --> 00:39:28.920
as can clearly be seen, as many
as 45% of the citizens scored 6 or 7

00:39:29.080 --> 00:39:34.880
and that must surely have some
positive effect on total literacy,

00:39:35.040 --> 00:39:38.200
although it is
naturally not sufficient.

00:39:38.360 --> 00:39:41.960
The international comparison
shows that we are placed

00:39:42.120 --> 00:39:48.080
somewhere at the
beginning of the last third, or so,

00:39:48.240 --> 00:39:51.320
somewhere between
Poland and Albania.

00:39:51.480 --> 00:39:57.280
I do not think that we can be
happy with our present position,

00:39:57.440 --> 00:40:00.160
but then there is
room for improvement.

00:40:00.320 --> 00:40:03.520
At this point, and at this point
only, our methodology differed

00:40:03.680 --> 00:40:06.240
from the methodology
used by other countries.

00:40:06.400 --> 00:40:09.640
Until 2012, literacy
carried a score of 8,

00:40:09.800 --> 00:40:12.000
but then one
question was eliminated

00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:14.200
as it was not
discriminating,

00:40:14.360 --> 00:40:16.440
since almost everyone
gave a yes answer.

00:40:16.600 --> 00:40:21.560
So we had to adjust it slightly
to make this comparison.

00:40:21.720 --> 00:40:24.680
The OECD is also
working continuously

00:40:24.840 --> 00:40:29.080
on this measuring
instrument to improve it.

00:40:29.240 --> 00:40:32.760
Another component that
makes a very big contribution

00:40:32.920 --> 00:40:37.880
to the assessment of financial
literacy is financial behaviour.

00:40:38.040 --> 00:40:42.280
The total score achieved
was 4.6 out of the total of 9.

00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:45.400
Here, as we can see,
we are in the middle,

00:40:45.560 --> 00:40:47.960
or slightly
above the middle.

00:40:48.120 --> 00:40:52.240
And we can see that the
young scored the lowest

00:40:52.400 --> 00:40:57.120
on the scale of financial behaviour,
both of the groups of the young,

00:40:57.280 --> 00:41:00.880
which is, let's say, expected to an
extent, justified and understood.

00:41:01.040 --> 00:41:06.280
Low-educated and
lower income individuals

00:41:06.440 --> 00:41:10.240
were the next
lowest scoring group

00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:14.120
while individuals
in the Zagreb region

00:41:14.280 --> 00:41:18.240
and in large cities with
population over 100 000

00:41:18.400 --> 00:41:22.040
scored the highest on the
scale of financial behaviour.

00:41:22.200 --> 00:41:25.240
There are 3 such
cities in Croatia.

00:41:25.400 --> 00:41:31.000
Financial behaviour is
defined by a range of questions

00:41:31.160 --> 00:41:34.600
prescribed by the
OECD and we can see

00:41:34.760 --> 00:41:39.280
that between four-fifths and
two-thirds of citizens carefully

00:41:39.440 --> 00:41:43.560
consider every
purchase, pay bills on time,

00:41:43.720 --> 00:41:46.920
prudently manage
their finances,

00:41:47.080 --> 00:41:51.680
keep or have something that might
be termed a household budget,

00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:54.680
which means that at the
beginning of the month

00:41:54.840 --> 00:41:57.680
they allocate the
spending money rationally

00:41:57.840 --> 00:42:00.760
so that we can say that
almost two-thirds of citizens

00:42:00.920 --> 00:42:03.080
make some
kind of effort

00:42:03.240 --> 00:42:07.760
to manage their household
budgets within the set limits.

00:42:07.920 --> 00:42:11.360
Sadly, fewer than half of them
have set long-term objectives.

00:42:11.520 --> 00:42:14.120
This survey does not
show why this is so,

00:42:14.280 --> 00:42:16.360
but the poor
financial situation

00:42:16.520 --> 00:42:19.200
probably prevents more
people from doing so.

00:42:19.360 --> 00:42:22.600
And now we come to two
questions which point to the need

00:42:22.760 --> 00:42:25.800
for a response of some kind,
or which call for greater caution,

00:42:25.960 --> 00:42:31.120
as only 16% of respondents try
to make their financial decisions

00:42:31.280 --> 00:42:36.360
after considering
several sources,

00:42:36.520 --> 00:42:41.080
or make a serious effort
before taking a decision.

00:42:41.240 --> 00:42:43.720
This is a very
low percentage

00:42:43.880 --> 00:42:47.800
and regardless of the effort
taken by two-thirds of the citizens,

00:42:47.960 --> 00:42:50.960
it is obvious that
one-fifth, or every fifth citizen

00:42:51.120 --> 00:42:54.400
has over the last year
been in a situation

00:42:54.560 --> 00:42:58.160
where he/she was unable to
cover his/her regular expenses

00:42:58.320 --> 00:43:04.560
and had to resort to some kind
of loan or something like that.

00:43:04.720 --> 00:43:10.400
And what's interesting and makes
the task of all the participants

00:43:10.560 --> 00:43:13.680
in this discussion on improving
financial literacy more difficult

00:43:13.840 --> 00:43:17.040
is the relatively low or we
can say very low correlation

00:43:17.200 --> 00:43:20.760
between financial knowledge
and financial behaviour.

00:43:20.920 --> 00:43:24.920
We would all be happy to see that
it is at least over 5, 6, but it is not.

00:43:25.080 --> 00:43:27.720
The same is true of
some other countries.

00:43:27.880 --> 00:43:33.640
This survey does not analyse
why this correlation is so low.

00:43:33.800 --> 00:43:39.280
However, I think each of us knows
a number of very educated people

00:43:39.440 --> 00:43:43.880
who took loans in Swiss
francs, far above their means.

00:43:44.040 --> 00:43:48.640
I think that in all
governments there were

00:43:48.800 --> 00:43:52.640
finance and economy
ministers who did that,

00:43:52.800 --> 00:43:57.040
I am sure there are people here
who know everything about this,

00:43:57.200 --> 00:43:59.640
but nevertheless
did the same thing.

00:43:59.800 --> 00:44:06.480
So I think this link, this correlation
is low, but that this is realistic.

00:44:06.640 --> 00:44:12.240
Let me tell you about an anecdote
from Nikola Tesla's biography

00:44:12.400 --> 00:44:15.280
that I read about recently. A few
months after he arrived in Paris,

00:44:15.440 --> 00:44:18.200
already a well-known
and well-paid engineer,

00:44:18.360 --> 00:44:20.760
his boss asked him how he
was doing there, he replied,

00:44:20.920 --> 00:44:23.000
"Superb,
everything's perfect,

00:44:23.160 --> 00:44:26.400
I only find the last 29 days of
the month to be the most difficult".

00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:29.320
So, the man would also
spend everything on the first day,

00:44:29.480 --> 00:44:33.560
and surely he would have solved all
these questions with a score of 21,

00:44:33.720 --> 00:44:38.400
so obviously there must be
something in addition to knowledge

00:44:38.560 --> 00:44:40.880
that affects our behaviour.
Knowledge is important,

00:44:41.040 --> 00:44:44.040
one can and must work on it,
but it is evidently not sufficient

00:44:44.200 --> 00:44:49.000
to ensure the behaviour which
will ensure household stability

00:44:49.160 --> 00:44:52.840
and by extension, the
stability of the entire country.

00:44:53.000 --> 00:44:56.200
And we can see that
in terms of behaviour

00:44:56.360 --> 00:45:00.560
we score lower
than other countries.

00:45:00.720 --> 00:45:05.480
Although some countries, such as
the Czech Republic and Hungary,

00:45:05.640 --> 00:45:10.480
which scored better in knowledge,
were in the same group as us.

00:45:10.640 --> 00:45:16.400
Germans scored the best,
Poland comes as a little surprise,

00:45:16.560 --> 00:45:19.080
but that is somehow
how it turns out.

00:45:19.240 --> 00:45:22.960
These northern countries
are a little more inclined

00:45:23.120 --> 00:45:27.720
towards a more rational
behaviour than those in the south.

00:45:29.960 --> 00:45:34.480
And now, attitude towards money,
i.e. savings and consumption.

00:45:34.640 --> 00:45:40.960
This is a component which
clearly affects the overall literacy.

00:45:41.120 --> 00:45:47.200
Under the OECD methodology, it is
based on these 3 statements only,

00:45:47.360 --> 00:45:51.480
the level of
agreement or disagreement

00:45:51.640 --> 00:45:53.920
with these
three statements.

00:45:54.080 --> 00:46:00.480
Croatian citizens scored on average
3 out of the maximum 5 points,

00:46:00.640 --> 00:46:05.920
a result similar to, I would say,
that obtained in knowledge

00:46:06.080 --> 00:46:11.200
and slightly better
than in behaviour.

00:46:11.360 --> 00:46:17.320
When you see these statements,
they are rather, rather explicit.

00:46:17.480 --> 00:46:21.320
The question on whether
one tends to live for today

00:46:21.480 --> 00:46:23.840
and let tomorrow
take care of itself,

00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:26.600
as many as 30% of citizens
agree with this attitude;

00:46:26.760 --> 00:46:29.320
28% of citizens prefer
to spend the money

00:46:29.480 --> 00:46:31.880
than to save it
for the long term;

00:46:32.040 --> 00:46:35.200
and every other citizen finds
that money should be spent.

00:46:35.360 --> 00:46:37.960
Maybe more people
should believe that,

00:46:38.120 --> 00:46:42.400
but this attitude
is predominant.

00:46:42.560 --> 00:46:47.800
It is interesting that there are no
statistically significant differences

00:46:47.960 --> 00:46:51.120
between citizens
across Croatia

00:46:51.280 --> 00:46:54.720
in their attitude towards
savings and consumption,

00:46:54.880 --> 00:46:58.960
only that the youngest respondents
were the least responsible

00:46:59.120 --> 00:47:01.640
when it came to
attitude towards money.

00:47:01.800 --> 00:47:04.440
There are probably a
number of very simple reasons

00:47:04.600 --> 00:47:07.080
that can
account for this.

00:47:07.240 --> 00:47:13.360
Compared with other countries,
here we have scored the highest.

00:47:13.520 --> 00:47:19.520
Here we scored best in
comparison with other countries.

00:47:19.680 --> 00:47:22.800
In other words, our position
here is not so bad after all.

00:47:22.960 --> 00:47:25.680
Maybe this can be explained
by the different crisis periods

00:47:25.840 --> 00:47:28.280
that we have been
through and people realised

00:47:28.440 --> 00:47:31.080
that they cannot spend
more than they can afford,

00:47:31.240 --> 00:47:34.160
so we have come slightly closer
to other countries in this respect.

00:47:34.320 --> 00:47:37.320
And now that we have gone
through all the three components

00:47:37.480 --> 00:47:40.800
of financial literacy, we
have come to the main topic

00:47:40.960 --> 00:47:43.360
and the main slide
of this presentation

00:47:43.520 --> 00:47:49.520
which shows our average
score of 11.7 out of the total of 21

00:47:49.680 --> 00:47:55.520
for the financial
literacy level in Croatia.

00:47:55.680 --> 00:48:01.200
Unfortunately, the OECD materials
available on the Internet or here

00:48:01.360 --> 00:48:04.600
do not provide averages
across other countries

00:48:04.760 --> 00:48:08.400
so we do not have comparisons
with them but we will try to find out,

00:48:08.560 --> 00:48:12.160
probably with others, what they
are, at least for some countries.

00:48:12.320 --> 00:48:15.640
Here again we see that
those below the age of 19

00:48:15.800 --> 00:48:19.000
scored the lowest on
the financial literacy scale

00:48:19.160 --> 00:48:24.200
and this clearly shows where
the focus should be placed,

00:48:24.360 --> 00:48:27.880
but there is an issue that
has been less researched,

00:48:28.040 --> 00:48:32.720
and that is the fact that
people older than them

00:48:32.880 --> 00:48:37.160
also have a very low level,
and this is all very low,

00:48:37.320 --> 00:48:39.960
low level of
financial literacy,

00:48:40.120 --> 00:48:42.880
and yet they might be
making important decisions.

00:48:43.040 --> 00:48:45.400
People aged 30 to
40 may be making

00:48:45.560 --> 00:48:49.280
important financial decisions, taking
long-term loans, short-term loans,

00:48:49.440 --> 00:48:51.680
taking out life
insurance policies.

00:48:51.840 --> 00:48:54.000
They might make
more complex decisions

00:48:54.160 --> 00:48:58.320
and yet are not highly
financially literate.

00:48:58.480 --> 00:49:01.640
The materials
provide data

00:49:01.800 --> 00:49:04.840
according to these
different age groups as well,

00:49:05.000 --> 00:49:08.240
so it is evident that the task of
the organiser of this gathering

00:49:08.400 --> 00:49:11.640
and the people responsible for
this issue is even more complex.

00:49:11.800 --> 00:49:15.200
They do know it is complex,
but it seems even more complex

00:49:15.360 --> 00:49:18.880
and demanding, but we are all
here to work and improve things.

00:49:19.040 --> 00:49:21.120
Highly
educated people

00:49:21.280 --> 00:49:25.040
have the highest
level of financial literacy,

00:49:25.200 --> 00:49:29.480
so we can see here that knowledge
after all does affect literacy,

00:49:29.640 --> 00:49:31.840
as does having a
higher income level

00:49:32.000 --> 00:49:37.480
and living in a city with a
population over 100 000.

00:49:37.640 --> 00:49:39.920
We have made
another analysis

00:49:40.080 --> 00:49:44.000
of the effects of the components of
financial literacy on the total result

00:49:44.160 --> 00:49:49.600
and here we see that, having
normalised all these scales,

00:49:49.760 --> 00:49:53.680
which run from 1 to
7, 1 to 9 and 1 to 5,

00:49:53.840 --> 00:49:57.040
and used a
scale of 1 to 5,

00:49:57.200 --> 00:50:03.720
financial knowledge and the
attitude towards spending money

00:50:03.880 --> 00:50:06.000
are somewhat
better rated

00:50:06.160 --> 00:50:09.400
while financial
behaviour is rated the worst.

00:50:09.560 --> 00:50:13.080
However, the conclusion
and the recommendation

00:50:13.240 --> 00:50:17.480
for all those involved in
the education of citizens is

00:50:17.640 --> 00:50:21.000
that all the three
components need to be worked on

00:50:21.160 --> 00:50:23.680
as these 3's are
very average grades

00:50:23.840 --> 00:50:27.800
and obviously are not sufficient for
making sound financial decisions

00:50:27.960 --> 00:50:33.960
to enable a more
secure life for the citizens

00:50:34.120 --> 00:50:37.560
and fewer
problems for all of us.

00:50:37.720 --> 00:50:41.600
But the results show
that in education

00:50:41.760 --> 00:50:45.840
one should place a
particular focus on the young,

00:50:46.000 --> 00:50:48.160
and possibly on
older individuals,

00:50:48.320 --> 00:50:50.520
although this is
maybe less important;

00:50:50.680 --> 00:50:53.680
the most vulnerable individuals
are people with lower income

00:50:53.840 --> 00:50:57.720
and low education, because
they must also make decisions

00:50:57.880 --> 00:51:00.240
in this financial world
regardless of their age,

00:51:00.400 --> 00:51:04.280
and they need to be
educated and assisted.

00:51:04.440 --> 00:51:06.960
Now that we are
talking about education,

00:51:07.120 --> 00:51:11.360
we hear people talk about
banning this or that product.

00:51:11.520 --> 00:51:15.560
If that ever made any sense, with
the entry into the European Union,

00:51:15.720 --> 00:51:17.760
the expansion
of the Internet,

00:51:17.920 --> 00:51:20.600
the offer of such
services over the Internet,

00:51:20.760 --> 00:51:25.760
I think this is a tool that will not
help much, or probably not at all.

00:51:25.920 --> 00:51:29.560
It is essential to educate
people, because despite bans,

00:51:29.720 --> 00:51:32.440
people still have
so many possibilities

00:51:32.600 --> 00:51:38.320
and if they make any mistake, we
are left to deal with those bankrupt,

00:51:38.480 --> 00:51:40.880
blocked, or
discontented people.

00:51:41.040 --> 00:51:44.400
Therefore it is our job to
improve their knowledge

00:51:44.560 --> 00:51:49.120
rather than impose
bans and warnings.

00:51:50.040 --> 00:51:54.320
This was the main subject of
the survey, its main objective,

00:51:54.480 --> 00:51:58.640
to look into the level of
financial literacy in Croatia.

00:51:58.800 --> 00:52:04.640
The survey also covered several
other areas with a few questions

00:52:04.800 --> 00:52:08.640
and we will show
their results now.

00:52:08.800 --> 00:52:11.160
One of them is
finance management

00:52:11.320 --> 00:52:14.240
and we see here again something
that has been mentioned,

00:52:14.400 --> 00:52:18.520
that over two-thirds of the
citizens have some kind of budget,

00:52:18.680 --> 00:52:22.800
which implies some kind
of monthly financial plans.

00:52:22.960 --> 00:52:25.920
As many as two-thirds
somehow manage to save money,

00:52:26.080 --> 00:52:31.760
some of them keep the money
at home, earning no interest,

00:52:31.920 --> 00:52:34.840
and we see that every
other Croatian citizen

00:52:35.000 --> 00:52:38.080
saves money in this way.
This has not been investigated,

00:52:38.240 --> 00:52:41.040
but this probably involves
smaller amounts of money

00:52:41.200 --> 00:52:45.840
and what is worrying is that
practically every other citizen

00:52:46.000 --> 00:52:49.600
or household would not be able
to cover an unexpected expense

00:52:49.760 --> 00:52:52.080
equivalent to a
month’s income.

00:52:52.240 --> 00:52:55.480
If we look at these three
components together,

00:52:55.640 --> 00:53:02.120
we can see that two-thirds of
citizens could cover living expenses

00:53:02.280 --> 00:53:10.080
for a maximum period of 3
months, if they lost their income.

00:53:10.240 --> 00:53:13.280
So, 3 months is
the maximum period

00:53:13.440 --> 00:53:15.600
which people
could survive for

00:53:15.760 --> 00:53:20.480
if they lost their
main source of income.

00:53:20.640 --> 00:53:24.120
For one-fourth of the citizens,
this is only one month.

00:53:24.280 --> 00:53:28.080
And this shows that the citizens
have exhausted their reserves,

00:53:28.240 --> 00:53:30.880
what they used to have,
whether money or some assets.

00:53:31.040 --> 00:53:37.400
Periods of having to survive after
loss of the main source of income,

00:53:37.560 --> 00:53:43.240
which every dismissal implies, are
very, very dangerous and stressful

00:53:43.400 --> 00:53:46.680
for Croatian citizens.

00:53:46.840 --> 00:53:49.640
This part also covers
pension planning.

00:53:49.800 --> 00:53:54.680
We can see that 90% of the citizens
have a certain pension plan,

00:53:54.840 --> 00:54:00.160
but almost one-third or a little
over one-fourth are not sure

00:54:00.320 --> 00:54:03.480
if that plan is sound
and sustainable.

00:54:03.640 --> 00:54:10.200
And we see that 74 % of the people
count on the first pension pillar;

00:54:10.360 --> 00:54:14.480
all those employed or to be
employed are familiar with this;

00:54:14.640 --> 00:54:17.920
people in general are familiar
with the first pension pillar.

00:54:18.080 --> 00:54:20.800
It is interesting that as
many as 55% of the citizens

00:54:20.960 --> 00:54:23.400
include the second
pension pillar in their plans.

00:54:23.560 --> 00:54:26.240
This shows that an
awareness of this second pillar

00:54:26.400 --> 00:54:28.840
as something that
can be counted on,

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:32.520
does exist among the citizens
and that it is very widespread.

00:54:32.680 --> 00:54:36.440
We see here that 27% of
respondents rely on their spouses

00:54:36.600 --> 00:54:41.120
and partners. These people do not
count on the first pension pillar.

00:54:41.280 --> 00:54:44.480
Evidently, these people have
never been in the labour market

00:54:44.640 --> 00:54:47.160
and do not
have anything else.

00:54:47.320 --> 00:54:51.400
Now people also count on
occasional work in retirement

00:54:51.560 --> 00:54:53.720
as many as
one-fourth of them,

00:54:53.880 --> 00:54:55.960
which is a relatively
high proportion,

00:54:56.120 --> 00:54:58.400
and I would say
this was optimistic,

00:54:58.560 --> 00:55:01.160
it is normal for people
to be a little optimistic

00:55:01.320 --> 00:55:05.000
and there are still people, although
their number is decreasing,

00:55:05.160 --> 00:55:08.680
who can finance a
part of their retirement

00:55:08.840 --> 00:55:15.480
by selling or using their
financial or tangible assets.

00:55:16.120 --> 00:55:19.400
And now about financial
products and services,

00:55:19.560 --> 00:55:23.480
knowledge and use
of financial products.

00:55:23.640 --> 00:55:27.440
Only 9% of citizens do not
use financial products at all

00:55:27.600 --> 00:55:31.960
and only 1% of them are
not familiar with any of them.

00:55:32.120 --> 00:55:35.960
This means that the knowledge
and use of financial products

00:55:36.120 --> 00:55:38.600
is very widespread

00:55:38.760 --> 00:55:41.840
and 62% of citizens
shop around thoroughly

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:49.080
before negotiating financial
services but 14% of them

00:55:49.240 --> 00:55:53.880
negotiate them without
considering other options,

00:55:54.040 --> 00:55:57.360
which means that
they choose a product,

00:55:57.520 --> 00:56:02.680
make some enquiries about it
and then make a final decision.

00:56:02.840 --> 00:56:07.480
What is interesting for the
banks, insurance companies, etc.

00:56:07.640 --> 00:56:10.920
involved in
retail business,

00:56:11.080 --> 00:56:16.040
is that every other citizen is very
much influenced by the information

00:56:16.200 --> 00:56:21.720
obtained by the loan clerk
and by the attitude of that clerk.

00:56:21.880 --> 00:56:26.800
Only 13% of citizens do not use a
giro or a current account in a bank.

00:56:26.960 --> 00:56:29.840
These are the
unemployed and individuals

00:56:30.000 --> 00:56:33.920
who are not in the
working age population.

00:56:34.080 --> 00:56:37.920
The understanding of financial
products grows, naturally,

00:56:38.080 --> 00:56:43.000
with the level of
education and monthly income.

00:56:43.160 --> 00:56:48.000
One of the topics also
included financial survival strategy.

00:56:48.160 --> 00:56:52.080
The issue of
making ends meet

00:56:52.240 --> 00:56:56.040
was also covered
by several questions,

00:56:56.200 --> 00:57:00.720
and we have some
interesting results here.

00:57:00.880 --> 00:57:05.840
As many as one third of
the citizens had problems

00:57:06.000 --> 00:57:11.360
covering their living
expenses in the last 12 months.

00:57:11.520 --> 00:57:14.520
This is a very high
percentage in my opinion,

00:57:14.680 --> 00:57:19.400
and it points to the complexity
of the situation in Croatia.

00:57:19.560 --> 00:57:23.760
Of the total number of respondents,
20% in such situations resorted to

00:57:23.920 --> 00:57:28.280
cutting back on
spending and doing without

00:57:28.440 --> 00:57:31.200
to manage until the
end of the month.

00:57:31.360 --> 00:57:35.440
These 20%, about two thirds
of the citizens with difficulties

00:57:35.600 --> 00:57:39.320
and 11% of the total, which
is again one third of those,

00:57:39.480 --> 00:57:42.280
borrowed money
from family and friends,

00:57:42.440 --> 00:57:46.680
bridging the gap in this way
or by a combination of the two.

00:57:46.840 --> 00:57:49.600
A very small
percentage of respondents

00:57:49.760 --> 00:57:53.520
took out a short-term
or a cash loan.

00:57:53.680 --> 00:57:56.680
This also
reveals something

00:57:56.840 --> 00:57:59.960
in connection with the
behaviour of citizens;

00:58:00.120 --> 00:58:05.000
the authorised overdraft for
covering unexpected costs

00:58:05.160 --> 00:58:10.320
or those costs that cannot
be covered by regular income;

00:58:10.480 --> 00:58:13.640
the authorised current
account overdraft is used

00:58:13.800 --> 00:58:17.320
as a rather expensive
source, payments are deferred,

00:58:17.480 --> 00:58:21.040
but only a small number of people
do that, the use of credit card.

00:58:21.200 --> 00:58:23.400
I am not sure whether
people still believe

00:58:23.560 --> 00:58:26.640
that they can use one credit card
to pay the charges of another one,

00:58:26.800 --> 00:58:30.400
but it seems so; the use of
an unauthorised overdraft,

00:58:30.560 --> 00:58:34.200
which is even worse,
and taking out a loan.

00:58:34.360 --> 00:58:39.760
We can see that to cover living
expenses when in financial trouble,

00:58:39.920 --> 00:58:43.840
people use
different strategies.

00:58:44.000 --> 00:58:46.360
And now we come
again to attitudes;

00:58:46.520 --> 00:58:49.960
this was another component
investigated by the OECD survey,

00:58:50.120 --> 00:58:53.560
we look into the attitudes
towards savings and consumption

00:58:53.720 --> 00:58:56.920
in more detail. There are only
a few questions on this topic.

00:58:57.080 --> 00:59:00.480
We can see that 63% of
citizens carefully manage

00:59:00.640 --> 00:59:03.520
their financial transaction

00:59:03.680 --> 00:59:06.680
and this is almost the same
percentage as that of people

00:59:06.840 --> 00:59:09.080
who have what is called
a household budget,

00:59:09.240 --> 00:59:12.600
i.e. allocations made at
the beginning of the month

00:59:12.760 --> 00:59:17.480
or when they receive their income
to cover their basic expenses.

00:59:17.640 --> 00:59:22.240
As many as every
fifth citizen in Croatia

00:59:22.400 --> 00:59:25.360
believes that he/she
has too much debt,

00:59:25.520 --> 00:59:29.320
which is approximately the
same as the number of people

00:59:29.480 --> 00:59:35.360
with frozen accounts and who
have loans above their means.

00:59:35.520 --> 00:59:41.560
As many as 38% or
almost two-fifths are satisfied

00:59:41.720 --> 00:59:45.640
or very satisfied with their financial
situation, which does not mean

00:59:45.800 --> 00:59:50.480
that they are all wealthy, they are
simply aware of their possibilities,

00:59:50.640 --> 00:59:54.920
where they stand and they are
happy with the way things are.

00:59:55.080 --> 00:59:57.480
And then again,
two-fifths say

00:59:57.640 --> 01:00:00.600
that the financial
situation prevents them

01:00:00.760 --> 01:00:04.800
from doing things
they would like to do.

01:00:04.960 --> 01:00:09.920
Regarding the attitudes towards
savings and consumption,

01:00:10.080 --> 01:00:13.680
there were a
number of statements

01:00:13.840 --> 01:00:17.560
where 1 represented strong
agreement with a statement

01:00:17.720 --> 01:00:20.200
and 3 strong
disagreement with a statement

01:00:20.360 --> 01:00:24.480
and we can see that people
largely agreed with the statements

01:00:24.640 --> 01:00:30.680
pointing to a more responsible
attitude towards consumption,

01:00:30.840 --> 01:00:36.720
savings, etc. Here we can see that
half of the respondents, or 50%

01:00:36.880 --> 01:00:39.280
agreed with
"money should be spent"

01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:42.920
and we can also see that
these have too much debt

01:00:43.080 --> 01:00:46.160
and that a relatively small
number of people agreed,

01:00:46.320 --> 01:00:49.400
i.e. some one-fifth said that
they rather spent long-term

01:00:49.560 --> 01:00:51.880
than saved
long-term and that they

01:00:52.040 --> 01:00:54.920
"tended to live for today and
let tomorrow take care of itself."

01:00:55.080 --> 01:00:57.120
We all know
people like that,

01:00:57.280 --> 01:01:01.560
there may be more of them
than the survey has revealed.

01:01:01.720 --> 01:01:03.840
And now, instead
of a conclusion,

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:07.520
and of course, the final
conclusion and action plans

01:01:07.680 --> 01:01:11.120
and what needs to be done next
will be made by the colleagues

01:01:11.280 --> 01:01:14.200
from the CNB, Hanfa and the
Ministry and all other actors

01:01:14.360 --> 01:01:17.440
responsible for education and
development of financial literacy.

01:01:17.600 --> 01:01:24.440
What appeared interesting to us is
that several independent questions

01:01:24.600 --> 01:01:28.320
or groups of questions show
that Croatians are generally

01:01:28.480 --> 01:01:34.360
a risk-averse population and
that almost two thirds of them

01:01:34.520 --> 01:01:37.760
have a household
budget, pay bills on time,

01:01:37.920 --> 01:01:40.440
do not spend
money in advance, etc.

01:01:40.600 --> 01:01:44.200
It is a fact that
one-third or more citizens,

01:01:44.360 --> 01:01:47.280
which is a large
number of citizens,

01:01:47.440 --> 01:01:51.000
have found themselves in big
trouble and are very loud about it,

01:01:51.160 --> 01:01:53.480
which is expected
and legitimate;

01:01:53.640 --> 01:01:58.000
but sometimes we forget the
fact that most of the citizens

01:01:58.160 --> 01:02:01.640
try to live within
their means,

01:02:01.800 --> 01:02:08.240
behaving with
maximum responsibility,

01:02:08.400 --> 01:02:13.640
which is interesting.

01:02:15.040 --> 01:02:18.680
These results show that
education is most needed

01:02:18.840 --> 01:02:21.840
for citizens with lower
incomes and a lower education.

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:25.520
And as we have seen for
younger citizens as well.

01:02:25.680 --> 01:02:28.160
I would say that
the total result is such

01:02:28.320 --> 01:02:31.120
that it would warrant the
provision of education for all

01:02:31.280 --> 01:02:33.440
and maybe introduce
into the OECD criteria

01:02:33.600 --> 01:02:36.080
an element which they now
lack and that is the significance

01:02:36.240 --> 01:02:38.480
of the financial decisions
that these citizens make.

01:02:38.640 --> 01:02:41.280
This means that special
education should be provided

01:02:41.440 --> 01:02:43.720
to people at the age when
they can take out home loans.

01:02:43.880 --> 01:02:46.520
This is not so important for
let's say car purchase loans

01:02:46.680 --> 01:02:50.640
which are shorter term
and less dangerous.

01:02:50.800 --> 01:02:53.840
And it should be borne in mind that
knowledge alone is not sufficient.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:57.960
As can be seen in
other research and areas,

01:02:58.120 --> 01:03:02.480
there is a gap between
knowledge and behaviour,

01:03:02.640 --> 01:03:06.240
which is affected by
a number of factors,

01:03:06.400 --> 01:03:11.200
which means that we have to look
into and define the procedures

01:03:11.360 --> 01:03:13.920
for transferring
knowledge to behaviour

01:03:14.080 --> 01:03:16.720
and achieve changed
citizen behaviour.

01:03:16.880 --> 01:03:19.360
I think this is
the basic objective.

01:03:19.520 --> 01:03:22.040
Even if we were
all Nobel laureates,

01:03:22.200 --> 01:03:28.800
if we act impulsively and
we will hardly achieve that.

01:03:28.960 --> 01:03:32.040
Knowledge alone is not
sufficient. I would like to add

01:03:32.200 --> 01:03:35.400
what is often heard and that
is that bans are not possible,

01:03:35.560 --> 01:03:39.880
they can only remove
some of the responsibility.

01:03:40.040 --> 01:03:43.320
And naturally as
researchers, we looked into areas

01:03:43.480 --> 01:03:46.480
which remained uncovered and
which could be further investigated.

01:03:46.640 --> 01:03:50.000
One of these things is the
need for qualitative research

01:03:50.160 --> 01:03:53.320
which could provide us
with a better understanding

01:03:53.480 --> 01:03:56.080
of the financial
behaviour of citizens

01:03:56.240 --> 01:03:58.600
as we see can see it is
the most problematic,

01:03:58.760 --> 01:04:01.920
particularly the motivation and
reasons for some behaviour,

01:04:02.080 --> 01:04:07.120
where there is a low correlation
between knowledge and behaviour;

01:04:07.280 --> 01:04:10.200
this cannot be done by
quantitative research,

01:04:10.360 --> 01:04:12.440
it is done by
qualitative research,

01:04:12.600 --> 01:04:15.480
which is quite important for
the definition of activities

01:04:15.640 --> 01:04:18.040
involving these
groups of citizens.

01:04:18.200 --> 01:04:21.760
Another interesting thing
that the team came up with

01:04:21.920 --> 01:04:27.240
is the absence of
investigation of legal literacy.

01:04:27.400 --> 01:04:31.640
It is a fact that many
citizens, myself included,

01:04:31.800 --> 01:04:35.360
have a too casual approach
to entering into agreements

01:04:35.520 --> 01:04:39.320
with telecommunications
operators, financial agreements,

01:04:39.480 --> 01:04:44.720
or large purchase agreements,
etc., never reading what they say.

01:04:44.880 --> 01:04:48.560
Someone noticed this a long
time ago, we buy a device,

01:04:48.720 --> 01:04:51.480
open the box, find the
instructions, throw them away

01:04:51.640 --> 01:04:54.640
and turn on the device. No
one reads the instructions.

01:04:54.800 --> 01:04:58.600
So, we see there is a problem here,
even if one reads the instructions,

01:04:58.760 --> 01:05:01.040
he/she often does
not understand them.

01:05:01.200 --> 01:05:03.560
So maybe some basic
information or a warning,

01:05:03.720 --> 01:05:06.920
this is something that would
need to be further worked on.

01:05:07.080 --> 01:05:11.320
And as we realised that this
survey also aims to measure

01:05:11.480 --> 01:05:15.360
the activity of the regulators
or institutions responsible

01:05:15.520 --> 01:05:20.680
for raising the level of literacy,
our opinion as a research team is

01:05:20.840 --> 01:05:25.480
that the OECD
methodology is an excellent,

01:05:25.640 --> 01:05:30.120
though a little coarse tool, in the
sense that it has been provided

01:05:30.280 --> 01:05:33.280
to be used globally in
a consistent manner.

01:05:33.440 --> 01:05:38.080
Every country has its own
problems or specific characteristics

01:05:38.240 --> 01:05:42.280
which require
special focus

01:05:42.440 --> 01:05:46.800
and the results have to be seen
over shorter periods of time.

01:05:46.960 --> 01:05:49.120
This is why
there is a proposal

01:05:49.280 --> 01:05:53.080
that further research
measuring instruments be defined,

01:05:53.240 --> 01:05:56.360
which is not
easy, but possible.

01:05:56.520 --> 01:05:59.400
Measuring instruments
which would measure

01:05:59.560 --> 01:06:03.600
certain elements of financial
literacy with a little more precision

01:06:03.760 --> 01:06:07.360
and more focus in Croatia, which
may not have been captured

01:06:07.520 --> 01:06:11.200
by the OECD model which must
be such as to function globally

01:06:11.360 --> 01:06:17.280
and be perfect for global use.
And that would be all. Thank you.

01:06:30.560 --> 01:06:33.160
Once again, thank
you, Mr Dumičić.

01:06:33.320 --> 01:06:36.000
And now you
can ask questions

01:06:36.160 --> 01:06:40.320
which will be answered by
Mr Dumičić, the IPSOS team,

01:06:40.480 --> 01:06:42.960
or our colleagues
from the CNB, Hanfa

01:06:43.120 --> 01:06:45.120
and the
Ministry of Finance,

01:06:45.280 --> 01:06:48.400
depending on the nature
of your question. Please.

01:06:48.560 --> 01:06:53.520
We have microphones. Anyone,
colleagues from the media....

01:07:06.240 --> 01:07:08.480
If there are
no questions,

01:07:08.640 --> 01:07:12.360
I would like to thank you all for
coming on behalf of the hosts,

01:07:12.520 --> 01:07:15.560
the CNB and Hanfa and
would like to invite you

01:07:15.720 --> 01:07:20.720
to join us for an informal gathering
for further discussion on this topic.

01:07:20.880 --> 01:07:23.000
Thank you very much.

